    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-01-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-01-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="804"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d804">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14273.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams—Extracts.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 22, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Convention has approved the plan of government<note n="4" xml:id="d804fn4"
                        >Quoted in his January 14, 4 p.m.</note> as far as Article 7. Cabinet
                    ministers have been made individually and collectively responsible to the
                    Convention for their conduct.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
